      • getParametersForCell

        public GridLayout.GridParameters getParametersForCell(int row,
                                                      int col)
        Creates an instance of GridParameters which uses the cell at the given width and height to calculate the bounds within the container this instance of the layout belongs to.
        Parameters:
        row - The row within this layout of the cell.
        col - The column within this layout of the cell.
        Returns:
        An instance of GridParameters which represents the cell at row and col.

      • getParametersForCellsInRange

        public GridLayout.GridParameters getParametersForCellsInRange(int startRow,
                                                              int startCol,
                                                              int endRow,
                                                              int endCol)
        Creates an instance of GridParameters for the given range of cells, so that the parameters specify that the Component which these parameters are applied to should occupy that entire range of cells within the layout.
        Parameters:
        startRow - The row of the first cell in the range.
        startCol - The column of the first cell in the range.
        endRow - The row of the last cell in the range.
        endCol - The column of the last cell in the range.
        Returns:
        An instance of GridParameters which indicates that the component should occupy all of the cells within the range from the start (row, col) to the end (row, col), including the last cell in this range.

      • enableCells

      • getBounds

        public Region getBounds(java.lang.Object params)
        Description copied from interface: Layout
        Calculates the size of the Region that a Component may be placed within, using the given parameters object to make this calculation. The type of this object, as well as the way that it affects the determination of the bounds, is implementation-dependent. This method may throw an error if the type of this parameter is incorrect (because a client passed an incorrect parameter when constructing a Component).
        Specified by:
        getBounds in interface Layout
        Parameters:
        params - An object which describes the positioning information that will be used to calculate these bounds. This is implementation dependent, and the type of this object is likely to change between different Layouts.
        Returns:
        The bounds that the parameters object represents.
